The MBA/MIS sspecialisation is an advanced professional degree that combines management skills with the study of information systems analysis and design. The programme is designed to develop the student's ability to formulate and implement management information systems that will promote the achievement of the goals and objectives of the organisation. Emphasis is placed upon the theory of information systems analysis and the modelling of the decision-making process in designing effective information systems.
The MBA Management Information Systems is a two-year programme. The lectures are delivered through three (3) streams with ten (10) session weekends for each stream. This means that there is one-and-a-half year of coursework and one stream for seminars and a dissertation. A critical component is a Business and Networking Bootcamp, which brings together our students and some industry players for network building and fostering partnerships between our students and entrepreneurs and businesses.
